142.3	Tomato	Tomato	The word "tomato" may refer to the plant or the edible, typically red, fruit that it bears. Originating in South America, the tomato was spread around the world following the Spanish colonization of the Americas, and its many varieties are now widely grown, often in greenhouses in cooler climates.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Bright_red_tomato_and_cross_section02.jpg/250px-Bright_red_tomato_and_cross_section02.jpg
